Yet, as Rochberg lays out, ancient investigations of regularity and irregularity, norms and anomalies clearly established an axis of knowledge between the knower and an intelligible, ordered world. Rochberg is the first scholar to make a case for how exactly we can understand cuneiform knowledge, observation, prediction, and explanation in relation to science—without recourse to later ideas of nature. Systematically examining the whole of Mesopotamian science with a distinctive historical and methodological approach, Before Nature will open up surprising new pathways for studying the history of science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAssyro-Babylonian literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aAstronomy, Assyro-Babylonian. 0aLearning and scholarship - Assyria. 0aLearning and scholarshipzAssyria. 0aPhilosophy of naturezAssyria. 0aSciencezAssyria. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aBabylonian.  aastrology.  aastronomy.  acuneiform.  adivination.  aknowledge.  anature.  ascience.  ascientific imagination.  ascientific models.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311071098440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226406275423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226406275/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles